These problems are related to graph theory and optimization, which are typically covered in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-categories. The paper also involves combinatorial optimization, which falls under the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions information theory, which is covered in the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves complexity theory, which is typically covered in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
